ResetClosure receives a caller-provided fileio.Session (see fileio.session) whose lock is already held for the entire Load→modify→Save window. It loads State via the Session, scans the filesystem, reconciles specs and markers, re-derives closures from the current scan+baseline, and locates the closure with the matching 8-character hash. The core applies each event in the closure to baseline: NODE_CHANGED syncs the baseline hash to scan hash; EDGE_ADDED adds the edge to baseline; EDGE_REMOVED removes it; NODE_REMOVED deletes the node and filters its edges; EDGE_BROKEN is a no-op. Closures containing only broken-edge events are refused with ErrResetClosureOnlyBroken. The orchestrator saves the resulting State (Specs, Markers, Edges) via the Session, merging scanned spec-spec edges via mergeScannedEdges so newly-cited refs make it into state.xml. ErrResetClosureNotFound is returned when the hash doesn't match any current closure. See principles.friction.